<section class="article-hero">

<h1>How to Make Mac and Cheese Creamy</h1>

<p>
Perfect mac and cheese should be smooth, rich, and creamy.
These tips will help you avoid grainy or dry mac and cheese.
</p>

</section>

<section class="article-section">

<h2>1. Use a Roux</h2>

<p>
A roux (butter and flour cooked together) thickens the cheese
sauce and keeps it smooth.
</p>

<h2>2. Use Freshly Shredded Cheese</h2>

<p>
Pre-shredded cheese contains anti-caking agents that can make
sauce grainy.
</p>

<h2>3. Don't Overheat the Cheese</h2>

<p>
High heat can cause cheese to separate. Always melt cheese on
low heat.
</p>

<h2>4. Add Cream or Evaporated Milk</h2>

<p>
This increases richness and smoothness.
</p>

<h2>5. Add Cream Cheese</h2>

<p>
Just a few tablespoons can make mac incredibly creamy.
</p>

</section>

</main>

